Vehicle assembler General Motors East Africa (GMEA) is now Isuzu East Africa Ltd. The change of name took effect from August 1, after attaining the required regulatory approvals. Isuzu East Africa Managing Director Rita Kavashe said Isuzu would build on GMEA&rsquo;s 40-year heritage. &ldquo;As such, Isuzu East Africa is starting out from a solid foundation established by General Motors,&rdquo; said Ms Kavashe.&nbsp; Isuzu Motors acquired GM&rsquo;s 57.7 per cent shareholding in GMEA.&nbsp;